description:
&lt;p&gt;Partnering Health Group are an established and expanding healthcare organisation responsible for providing a variety of urgent and primary health care services across Hampshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity are now available for a&lt;strong&gt;Mental Nurse Practitioner&lt;/strong&gt;to work as a member of the multi-disciplinary Direct Clinical Assessment team in Lymington, New Forest Hampshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a&lt;strong&gt;Mental Health Nurse,&lt;/strong&gt;you will provide safe and effective care and specialist advice for people (18+) with a diverse mental health needs, psychological problems and psychiatric illnesses in order to support and refer them during the out of hours period.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, motivated, caring applicant to become part of our friendly and fun team in the lovely facilities at the Urgent Treatment Centre at Lymington Hospital. This is an exciting opportunity to come and work in a busy, dynamic environment where the focus is on teamwork providing excellent and efficient care to our local community by offering an alternative health care choice and reducing pressures on local Emergency departments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mental Health Practitioner Duties &amp; Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· 1st level Registered Mental Health Nurse with current registration with NMC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Experience of assessing and managing crisis with those with a severe mental illness&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Demonstrate experience of working with people who experience serious and ongoing mental health problems&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Able to make judgements based on evidence- based practice and translate this for use in the clinical team environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mental Health Practitioner Skills &amp; Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Degree level nurse practitioner&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Independent and supplementary nurse prescriber&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Competent in the use of IT systems, including Adastra, EMIS etc&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Sound knowledge of local Primary care services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Weekday evenings 18.30-22.00 and weekends flexible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The basic FTE salary is £44,499.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Partnering Health Group (PHL) are an established and expanding healthcare organisation responsible for providing a variety of urgent and primary health care services across Hampshire and are delighted to be providing the UTC in Lymington Hospital. The New Forest is a beautiful setting in which to provide high quality, safe services which improve the health, wellbeing and independence of the people we care for. We deliver these services to our community so you will feel a real sense of achievement and that your work makes a difference to local people’s lives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job Types: Part-time, Permanent&lt;/p&gt;
